    instead of an argument, so 'provision-all --help' prints usage rather than
    provisioning every domain.

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 20:00:00 -0400

dsmr-email-admin (1.0-3) trixie; urgency=low

  * authdns provision-all now skips any domain that already publishes an SPF or
    DKIM record: such a domain sends through another path (an external mail
    service or a different MTA), and installing a local key plus republishing
    its records would break that delivery.  --include-external overrides.  This
    makes bulk provisioning safe on a host where some virtual domains are
    hosted for mail but actually send elsewhere.

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 19:30:00 -0400

dsmr-email-admin (1.0-2) trixie; urgency=low

  * Add DKIM/SPF management for virtual domains so unsigned hosted domains can
    pass Gmail/Yahoo sender authentication.  New subcommands:
      - 'dkim list|genkey|show|verify': generate and install an RSA DKIM
        signing key (qmail-dkim signs the domain's outbound mail immediately)
        and verify the published key against the local one;
      - 'spf suggest|verify': recommend and check an SPF record for the
        sending host;
      - 'authdns provision|provision-all|status|report|verify': provision one
        or all domains, show per-domain DKIM/SPF/DMARC coverage, and emit a
        narrative findings report that classifies each domain and explains the
        deliverability ramifications (Gmail/Yahoo 550-5.7.26).
    The audit set includes the system domain (any keyed domain), not only the
    vpopmail virtual domains.  Records are written as copy-pasteable files to
    control/authdns/<domain> for manual DNS publication; no nameserver is ever
    written to.
  * Recommends openssl (key generation) and bind9-dnsutils (DNS verification).

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 18:00:00 -0400

dsmr-email-admin (1.0-1) trixie; urgency=low

  * Initial release.  Health-check and repair tool for the DSMR
    qmail/vpopmail/dovecot stack.  'check' runs a read-only audit; 'fix'
    repairs stale control/config left by create-if-absent postinsts (a low
    qmail softlimit, swapped vpopmail.pgsql password/database fields, a
    dovecot SQL conf out of sync with vpopmail.pgsql, and a stopped vpopmail
    PostgreSQL cluster); 'selftest' proves delivery and dovecot auth end to
    end with a throwaway vpopmail mailbox.

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 12:11:30 -0400
